article.headline: Indiana State 63, Bradley 61
article.story: ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Eric Gray had 15 points and Indiana State barely made a 22-point first-half lead stand up in a 63-61 victory over Bradley in the first round of the Missouri Valley Conference tournament on Friday night. David Moss added 13 points and Amani Daanish 12 for Indiana State (11-19, 6-13), which will play top-seeded Southern Illinois in the quarterfinals on Saturday. Indiana State, which had lost nine of its previous 12 games, won for the first time away from home. The Sycamores were 0-12 on the road and had been 0-3 at neutral sites. Lawrence Wright had 18 points and nine rebounds for Bradley (13-15, 6-13), which lost 10 of its last 12. Wright had six points in the final 3:30, including a dunk off an inbounds play that cut the gap to 59-57 with 58 seconds to go. Two free throws by Jeremy Crouch with 2.4 seconds to go made it a one-point game at 62-61. Daanish was fouled with one second left after a long inbounds pass and made one of two free throws. Patrick O'Bryant missed a baseball heave at the buzzer for Bradley. O'Bryant added 15 points and 14 rebounds for Bradley, his sixth double-double of the season. Indiana State shot 52 percent in the first half and led by as many as 22 points before Bradley narrowed the gap to 44-28 at the break. But the Sycamores scored only 19 points the rest of the way and ended with 36.5 percent shooting. Bradley began the game 3-for-17 and trailed 37-15 with 5:22 to go in the half. Marcellus Sommerville, an all-conference forward for Bradley who averages 17.9 points, was held to seven points on 3-for-10 shooting. It's only the second time all season in single digits for Sommerville.
